    <div class="grammar-content">
        <div class="grammar-top">
            <h1>Lesson Content</h1>
        </div>
        <h1 class="content-heading japanese-text">てください (te kudasai)</h1>
        <h2 class="content-subheading">How To Use</h2>
        <p class="content-para">Verb (て Form) + ください</p>
        <h2 class="content-subheading">Explanation</h2>
        <p class="content-para">To make a polite request to another person</p>
        <h2 class="content-subheading">Meaning</h2>
        <p class="content-para">"Please do... for me."</p>
        <h2 class="content-subheading">Examples</h2>
        <p class="content-para">
            <ruby>ちょっと</ruby><ruby>待<rp>(</rp><rt>ま</rt><rp>)</rp>ってください</ruby><br>
            <span>Please wait a moment.</span><br><br>

            <ruby>やってみてください。</ruby><br>
            <span>Give it a try!</span><br><br>

            <ruby>日本語<rp>(</rp><rt>にほんご</rt><rp>)</rp></ruby><ruby>を</ruby><ruby>教<rp>(</rp><rt>おし</rt><rp>)</rp>えてください</ruby><br>
            <span>Please teach me Japanese.</span><br><br>
        </p>


        <h1 class="content-heading japanese-text">てもいいです (temo ii desu)</h1>
        <h2 class="content-subheading">How To Use</h2>
        <p class="content-para">
            <table class="how-to-use" border="1" style="padding: 10px;">
                <tr>
                    <td>Verb (て form)</td>
                    <td rowspan="4">もいい（です）</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Noun + で</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>な-adjective + で</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>い-adjective + いくて</td>
                </tr>
            </table>
        </p>
        <h2 class="content-subheading">Explanation</h2>
        <p class="content-para">Describes an activity that is permitted. When you talk about doing something that's okay, you can turn it into a question like "Is it okay to do this?" by adding 〜てもいいですか. If someone asks if they can do something and you agree, you can either repeat the action using もいいです or just say "Okay." It's important to know that saying とてもいいです (very good) or just もいいです by itself isn't the right way to respond.</p>
        <h2 class="content-subheading">Meaning</h2>
        <p class="content-para">"is OK to ?"</p>
        <p class="content-para">"is alright to ?"</p>
        <p class="content-para">"may I ?"</p>
        <h2 class="content-subheading">Examples</h2>
        <p class="content-para japanese-text">
          <ruby>トイレ</ruby><ruby>に</ruby><ruby>行<rp>(</rp><rt>い</rt><rp>)</rp></ruby><ruby>ってもいいですか？</ruby><br>
          <span>Is it okay to go to the bathroom?</span><br><br>

          <ruby>私<rp>(</rp><rt>わたし</rt><rp>)</rp></ruby><ruby>も</ruby><ruby>一緒<rp>(</rp><rt>いっしょ</rt><rp>)</rp></ruby><ruby>に</ruby><ruby>行<rp>(</rp><rt>い</rt><rp>)</rp></ruby><ruby>っていい？</ruby><br>
          <span>Can I go together as well?</span><br><br>

          <ruby>一<rp>(</rp><rt>ひと</rt><rp>)</rp></ruby><ruby>つ</ruby><ruby>質問<rp>(</rp><rt>しつもん</rt><rp>)</rp></ruby><ruby>を</ruby><ruby>聞<rp>(</rp><rt>き</rt><rp>)</rp></ruby><ruby>いてもいいですか？</ruby><br>
          <span>May I ask one question?</span><br><br>

        </p>
        
        <h1 class="content-heading japanese-text">てはいけません (te wa ikemasen)</h1>
        <h2 class="content-subheading">How To Use</h2>
        <table class="how-to-use" border="1">
            <tr>
                <td>Verb (て form)</td>
                <td>
                    はいけない<br>
                    はいけません

                </td>
            </tr>
                
     
        </table>
        <h2 class="content-subheading">Explanation</h2>
        <p class="content-para">A strong prohibition, just like in rules and regulations. If someone requests permission and you want to say no, you can use てはいけません, but it might sound a bit strict unless you're in a position of authority.</p>
        <h2 class="content-subheading">Meaning</h2>
        <p class="content-para">"must not"</p>
        <p class="content-para">"may not"</p>
        <p class="content-para">"cannot"</p>
        <h2 class="content-subheading">Examples</h2>
        <p class="content-para japanese-text">
          <ruby style="color: black;">嘘<rp style="color: black;">(</rp><rt style="color: black;">うそ</rt><rp style="color: black;">)</rp></ruby>
          <ruby style="color: black;">を</ruby>
          <ruby style="color: black;">ついてはいけない</ruby><br>
          <span style="color: black;"><strong>You</strong> must not tell lies.</span><br><br>

          <ruby style="color: black;">室内<rp style="color: black;">(</rp><rt style="color: black;">しつない</rt><rp style="color: black;">)</rp></ruby>
          <ruby style="color: black;">で</ruby>
          <ruby style="color: black;">タバコ<rp></rp></ruby>
          <ruby style="color: black;">を</ruby>
          <ruby style="color: black;">吸<rp style="color: black;">(</rp><rt style="color: black;">す</rt><rp style="color: black;">)</rp></ruby>
          <ruby style="color: black;">ってはいけませんよ</ruby><br>
          <span style="color: black;"><strong>Smoking</strong> is not allowed indoors.</span><br><br>

          <ruby style="color: black;">授業中<rp style="color: black;">(</rp><rt style="color: black;">じゅぎょうちゅう</rt><rp style="color: black;">)</rp></ruby>
          <ruby style="color: black;">に</ruby>
          <ruby style="color: black;">携帯電話<rp style="color: black;">(</rp><rt style="color: black;">けいたいでんわ</rt><rp style="color: black;">)</rp></ruby>
          <ruby style="color: black;">を</ruby>
          <ruby style="color: black;">使<rp style="color: black;">(</rp><rt style="color: black;">つか</rt><rp style="color: black;">)</rp></ruby>
          <ruby style="color: black;">ってはいけません</ruby><br>
          <span style="color: black;"><strong>You</strong> must not use your mobile phone during class.</span><br><br>
        </p>
    </div>
    
    <div class="grammar-content">
      <div class="grammar-top">
          <h1 class="japanese-text">Cultural Insights: Japanese Tea Ceremony (<ruby>茶道</ruby> - Sadō)</h1>
      </div>
          
    <div class="section">
        <h2 class="content-subheading">What's the Tea Ceremony All About?</h2>
        <p class="content-para">The Japanese tea ceremony is a beautiful tradition filled with values like harmony, respect, purity, and calmness.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2 class="content-subheading">Why Is It Special?</h2>
        <p class="content-para">It's deeply connected to Zen Buddhism, teaching us to be present and find peace in the moment while sipping tea with others.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2 class="content-subheading">Where Does It Happen?</h2>
        <p class="content-para">People often gather in special tea rooms or tea houses with unique designs to create a calm and thoughtful atmosphere.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Add more sections as needed -->

    <div class="section">
        <h2 class="content-subheading">Tea Tools and Traditions</h2>
        <p class="content-para">Special tools are used for making and serving tea. Each tool has a special meaning, and the way tea is prepared is like a beautiful dance.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2 class="content-subheading">Tea Time as a Bonding Experience</h2>
        <p class="content-para">The tea ceremony is not just about tea; it's a chance for people to come together, share thoughts, and feel a sense of togetherness.</p>
    </div>
  
</div>
